The paper discusses the analysis of deep neural network models, specifically in the fields of computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP), which are typically covered under the arXiv CS sub-categories of cs.CV and cs.CL. The paper also mentions norm-based capacity control metrics and Power Law (PL) based metrics, which are commonly used in the field of machine learning (cs.LG) to evaluate the quality of models. Additionally, the paper discusses the Theory of Heavy-Tailed Self Regularization, which is a concept from the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural engineering (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, and cs.NE, in that order.
